      "target": {
        "kind": "pull_request",
        "title": "fix: harden diff and approval state writes",
        "body": "## Summary\n- harden approval index persistence with an atomic exclusive create path\n- treat corrupt approval index and diff state JSON as expired/missing state instead of crashing\n- add regression coverage for approval index races/corruption and SDK diff state corruption\n\nFixes #112.\nFixes #113.\n\n## Validation\n- `pnpm --config.minimum-release-age=0 run format`\n- `pnpm --config.minimum-release-age=0 run test`\n- `pnpm --config.minimum-release-age=0 run build && node --test dist/test/state.test.js dist/test/approval_id.test.js --test-name-pattern 'corrupt|approval index writes never overwrite|writeFileAtomicExclusive'`\n\n## Proof\nTargeted behavior proof for the review findings:\n\n```text\n✔ approval index writes never overwrite an existing approval ID mapping\n✔ corrupt approval index is treated as expired instead of crashing (#113)\n✔ writeFileAtomicExclusive creates private files without replacing existing targets\n✔ diffAndStore treats corrupt previous state as a miss and rewrites atomically (#112)\n✔ SDK diff primitives treat corrupt previous state as a miss (#112)\n```\n\nThe exclusive create path is covered by the no-overwrite/private-file regression above. It uses Node's exclusive file creation semantics and does not replace an existing target.\n",
